commit.message: Merge branch 'jpellegrini-trig'
Merge branch 'trig' of https://github.com/jpellegrini/STklos into jpellegrini-trig
Comment the test on STk_primordial which was not so clear

Make (acos 1) return exact zero

Previously we had

stklos> (acos 1)
0.0
stklos> (asin 0)
0

Hm, we have anice precise result for `(asin 0)`, why not for
`(acos 1)`?   It's because for asin, we have:

```
    case tc_integer:  if (z == MAKE_INT(0)) return MAKE_INT(0);
                      return asin_real(INT_VAL(z));
```

and for acos, we were also testing for exact zero, and then we
returned inexact pi/2:

```
    case tc_integer:  if (z == MAKE_INT(0)) return div2(double2real(MY_PI),
                                                        MAKE_INT(2));
```

But that's not necessary, because `acos_real` will do that anyway. And
we were not testing for the nice case of `(acos 1)`. Now we do that.

One test was also adjusted.
Merge branch 'v210-apply'

Suppressed code for generating IN-APPLY instruction

There was some code for producing IN-APPLY instruction in the code, since a
looong time. In fact, producing this instruction doesn't reduce call times
(in général we finish by replacing a GREF_INVOKE by an IN-APPLY, and that's
all). Note that we still need to produce a PREPARE_CALL, since the call to
apply can be a closure applied in tail position.

Merge branch @jpellegrini 'parameter-peephole' + minor rewrites
Merge branch 'equiv'

Added a new instruction for inlining mem{q,v,oc}

The instruction takes an int to determine the operation to do
   1: memq
   2: memv
   3: member with two parameters
   4: member with three parameters

Added a new instruction for inlining ass{q,v,oc}

The instruction takes an int to determine the operation to do
   1: assq
   2: assv
   3: assoc with two parameters
   4: assoc with three parameters

Adding back the generation of IN_EQUAL VM instruction

This is possible now that equal? is fully written in C

Comment the equivp function

Comments are from the SRFI-85 Reference implementation
Small code reorganization
Get rid of the simple-equal function

Suppressed the redefinitions of member and assoc

They are no more necessary now that equal? is in C.

Small refactoring

Only equal? is exported now from boolean.c
Suppressed the file lib/equiv.stk (code for circular equal? in SCM)

Rewrite the R7RS equal? in C

This is a (dirty) first version. Must be simplified.

Added the %trace function for debugging

Call %debug if debug level is > 0

Suppressed the simple quote from readline quote chars

Needed for proper parenthesis flashing if enabled in the ~/.inputrc
file.
Merge branch 'jpellegrini-math-optimize'

Inline tables are list and no more A-lists

Simplified the inline tables: they are no more a-lists since the original
value of a symbol can be found back in the immutable SCHEME module.

Do not optimize equal? calls

In fact, we never produce the special instruction IN_EQUAL, since our version
of `equal?` is in Scheme (for infinite structures). After the rewriting of equiv?
in C, it will be possible to restore the optimization.
